By Ijeoma Okigbo Team Nigeria has arrived Kigali for KwibukaT20 Women’s Cricket tournament, with 24-man contingent, comprising 16 players and officials. Nigeria joins Uganda, Botswana and Brazil to arrive Rwanda for the tournament scheduled to begin on Thursday to June 18. It’s Nigeria’s second outing in Rwanda after they finished fourth place in 2021. The country’s first game is against 27th ranked Brazil—who are nine places ahead of the West African country, on Thursday. Meanwhile Kenya, Germany and Tanzania are still expected in Kigali. (NAN)(www.nannews.ng) ============ Edited by Idris Abdulrahman